        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Departmental Distinction: Students majoring in Geology can earn distinction, high distinction, and highest distinction upon graduation.  The requirements for these awards are:"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Distinction: A minimum cumulative grade point average of 3.3, and have also completed an approved independent study project, approved senior thesis, or approved capstone"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "High Distinction: A minimum cumulative grade point average of 3.5, and have also completed an approved independent study project, approved senior thesis, or approved capstone"
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": "Highest Distinction: A minimum cumulative grade point average of 3.7, and also completed an approved senior thesis or approved research capstone"
      },
      {
